* FEAR Boundary condition specification file
* * BC id = Boundary condition id input into Patran and appearing in the .ntl file
* * BC Type = BC type input into Patran
* * Flag1 = 0 for constant, read next line for constant value, 1 for function of time read the time dependant values into a vector
* * Flag2 = 0 unless this BC is a trajectory, 1 = POST style trajectory, 2 = CMA/FIAT style trajectory, 3 = time vs generic BC value  
* * FLAG3 = real number for constant spatial multipler, -1 for node based spatial field, -2 coordinate based spatial field, follows trajectory
* * Flag4 = 0 for scalar, 1 for vector --> only supported for BC's not a f(t), future upgrade will make vector BC types f(t)
* BC id   BCType   Flag1   Flag2  Flag3   Flag4
* BC #4 Aerodynamic heating in TPS surface
